question:
The train 160 m long is running with a speed of 80 km/hr. In what time will it pass a man running in same direction with the speed of 8 km/hr.A)16 seconds
B)8 seconds
C)15 seconds
D)6 seconds
E)28 seconds
rationale: Man and train are running in same direction, Relative Speed = 80 - 8 = 72 kmph. = (72 * 5)/18 = 20 m/sec Length of the train = 160 m. Time taken to pass the man = 160/20 = 8 seconds. Answer: Option B

B)64

rationale: class 1 have 3x student and class 2 have 5x student. 3x-15/5x-15=1/2,6x-30=5x-15,x=15 45+75=120 student answer A
